## STEP 3 — Build a Naive RAG Pipeline (UI App)

Using the generated test cases as the **knowledge base**, build an interactive **RAG pipeline web app** with the following features:

### 📄 Chunking Viewer Panel

- Display all test cases as individual **chunks**
- Each chunk should show: Test Case ID, Module, Title, and a preview of steps
- Allow the user to **browse/scroll through all chunks**

### 🔍 Retrieval Search Box

- A prominent text input where the user can type natural language queries
- Example queries:
  - *"Do we have a test case related to login?"*
  - *"Show me all high priority A/B testing test cases"*
  - *"Find test cases for password reset"*
- Use **semantic similarity / keyword matching** to retrieve the **top N most relevant test cases**
- Display matched test cases with a **relevance score or highlight**

### 💡 Regression Test Case Suggester

- Based on the retrieved results, use the RAG model to **suggest relevant regression test cases** to run
- Show a clean summary:
  > *"For your query about X, we recommend running these N test cases: [list]"*

